def: Of or pertaining to Asturias in Spain.-- n.
A complaint or complaining. [Obs.] E. Hall.
Pertaining to Abraham, the patriarch; as, the Abrachamiccovenant.
Cyanite or kyanite; -- so called in allusion to its unequalhardness in two different directions. See Cyanite.
One who has received the highest of the four minor orders inthe Catholic church, being ordained to carry the wine and water andthe lights at the Mass.
An obsolete wind instrument with a keyboard, in which thesound, which resembled the oboe, was produced by the vibration ofthin metallic plates, acted upon by blowing through a tube.
